name &quot;good person&quot;, like I do with all other things.<br>I live in Great Divide at the moment, and I have translocated more people than ever from here the last few weeks, it doesnt bother me in anyway. Its a small help I can provide for those that need it. <br>I make trips to solusek temple once in a while to refill the stock of tellie shards, but...cmon people...when you ask me for a translocate, I help you out of kindness, not greed. <br>Show me the respect not to treat me like a paid transport service...I would never turn down a stack of tellie shards, I will always turn down your platinum =)<br><br>Cinnamoon - concurrent resident of Great Divide <br>Spicy sorceress of Eternal Wrath<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukindridmorsaffero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KindridMorsAffero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/02 11:01:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=864.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you carry your own supply of portal fragments?</span><hr size=1> i never knew how much the components cost i see some wizards are trying to rip people off big time.  the max i will give for a port is 15 unless i am really in a need of a port.  the stingyness of wizards who wont do a TL when they are not in a group or if they are a group leader or something where they can easily do a tl is amazing.  all you do is cast a spell, 15plat for a ride when it costs you ~2plat to cast the spell, thats pretty good profit margin. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukindridmorsaffero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KindridMorsAffero</A> at: 1/30/02 11:03:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/02 11:10:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=864.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you carry your own supply of portal fragments?</span><hr size=1> I just gave one of my wizards 60 of them, and I know one of our Paladins uses the following method for asking for Translocates:<br><br>/auc Trading 10 Portal Fragments for TL to (location) <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,Guildleader: <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a>, Grandmaster <a href=http://www.base-nine.org/available_tinkering_items.htm>Tinkerer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ustrikefear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Strike Fear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/02 11:17:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=864.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you carry your own supply of portal fragments?</span><hr size=1> Well, that depends on whether or not your wizard or druid is made for the express purpose of making cash by porting people around.  They had to spend weeks leveling up that character so you could save some time and not have to hoof it all over Norrath or God forbid... ride a boat... *gasp.*<br><br>The question is not whether or not they are being greedy.  The question is how lazy are you and how much is worth to you to not burn a few hours running and riding boats from Odus to Faydwer?  They don't have to port you at all.  They're not there to provide an expected service for you just because it's within their power to get you somewhere faster.  Just because you might wait until it's a convenient time for the porter doesn't mean you're still going to get a ride.<br><br>If they do it free, it's out of the kindness of their heart.  Nowhere is written that their kindness is an expected given.  I like my car.  It keeps me from having to walk miles everywhere.  I don't expect car dealerships to give me a free car out of the kindness of their heart so I can get places faster.  A lot of work went in to making those vehicles even available to me if I should choose to purchase one... OR, I can just not give them anything and walk ;p<br><br>&quot;15plat for a ride when it costs you ~2plat to cast the spell, thats pretty good profit margin.&quot; <br><br>No... a pretty good profit margin is demonstrated by one of the vendors in Fungus Grove that I sold a &quot;Flute of the Sacred Glade&quot; to.  He gave me 50pp for it and was selling it afterwards for around 25K.  Now that's a good profit margin.  He's the one that taught me EQ economics.  You can blame him and Bill Gates for the lessons I've learned on the subject of profiteering.<br><br><br>Strike <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ustrikefear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Strike Fear</A> at: 1/30/02 11:48:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nydia>Nydia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/30/02 11:37:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=864.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you carry your own supply of portal fragments?</span><hr size=1> HTML Comments are not allowed <p></p><i></i></td></